{
  "title": "Micelles",
  "publicationStatus": "public",
  "labEnvironment": "production",
  "subtitle": "Explore potential energy of molecules in oil and water.",
  "category": "",
  "subCategory": "",
  "screenshot": "",
  "aspectRatio": 1.1,
  "fontScale": 1,
  "lang": "en-US",
  "i18nMetadata": "",
  "credits": "",
  "helpOnLoad": false,
  "aboutOnLoad": true,
  "about": [
    "Select an oil or water environment for molecules and observe how they are affected by interactions with ",
    "their environment and each other. These molecules have hydrophilic (polar) and hydrophobic (nonpolar) portions, ",
    "which interact in different ways with the surrounding environment. Watch how potential energy changes as the molecules ",
    "self-assemble into micelles.",
    "***",
    "*This simulation was developed by [the Interactions project](https://concord.org/projects/interactions \"the Interactions Project\") ",
    "with funding from the National Science Foundation (DRL-1232388) in partnership with ",
    "[the CREATE for STEM Institute](http://create4stem.msu.edu/ \"the CREATE for STEM Institute\") at Michigan State University. To learn more, ",
    "[visit the Interactions curriculum collection](https://learn.concord.org/interactions \"visit the Interactions curriculum collection\") in ",
    "which this simulation is embedded.*"
  ],
  "theme": "",
  "showTopBar": true,
  "showBottomBar": true,
  "padding": 10,
  "models": [
    {
      "type": "md2d",
      "id": "salt",
      "url": "models/lab-version/1/md2d/interactions/micelles/model.json",
      "onLoad": [
        "onStart(function() {",
        "  setComponentDisabled('drag', true);",
        "});",
        "onStop(function() {",
        "  setComponentDisabled('drag', false);",
        "});"
      ],
      "viewOptions": {
        "controlButtons": "play_reset",
        "controlButtonStyle": "text"
      }
    }
  ],
  "propertiesToRetain": [],
  "parameters": [
    {
      "name": "solvent",
      "initialValue": "water",
      "onChange": [
        "if (value === 'water') {",
        "  set('backgroundColor', '#A2E0F9');",
        "  setTextBoxProperties(0, {text: 'Water'})",
        "  setAtomProperties(3, {charge: 20})",
        "} else if (value === 'oil') {",
        "  set('backgroundColor', '#FFE200');",
        "  setTextBoxProperties(0, {text: 'Oil'})",
        "  setAtomProperties(3, {charge: -20})",
        "}"
      ]
    }
  ],
  "outputs": [],
  "filteredOutputs": [],
  "helpTips": [],
  "dataSets": [],
  "components": [
    {
      "id": "pe-graph",
      "type": "barGraph",
      "property": "potentialEnergy",
      "min": -150,
      "max": 40,
      "title": "Potential Energy",
      "titleOn": "right",
      "labels": 0,
      "units": false,
      "gridLines": 10,
      "labelFormat": "0.1f",
      "barWidth": "2em",
      "height": "100%",
      "barColor": "#e23c34",
      "fillColor": "#fff",
      "tooltip": "",
      "helpIcon": false
    },
    {
      "id": "solvent",
      "type": "radio",
      "style": "radio",
      "orientation": "horizontal",
      "label": "Set solvent",
      "labelOn": "left",
      "options": [
        {
          "text": "Water (polar)",
          "value": "water"
        },
        {
          "text": "Oil (non-polar)",
          "value": "oil"
        }
      ],
      "property": "solvent",
      "retainProperty": true,
      "disabled": false,
      "tooltip": "",
      "helpIcon": false
    },
    {
      "id": "drag",
      "type": "radio",
      "style": "radio",
      "orientation": "horizontal",
      "label": "Interact with molecules",
      "labelOn": "left",
      "options": [
        {
          "text": "Move molecule",
          "value": "translate"
        },
        {
          "text": "Rotate molecule",
          "value": "rotate"
        }
      ],
      "property": "onAtomDrag",
      "retainProperty": true,
      "disabled": false,
      "tooltip": "",
      "helpIcon": false
    }
  ],
  "layout": {
    "right": [
      "pe-graph"
    ],
    "bottom": [
      [
        "solvent"
      ],
      [
        "drag"
      ]
    ]
  },
  "template": "simple"
}
